# ğŸ§© **AGILE TECHNICAL TERMINOLOGY (With Clear Definitions)**

## ğŸ“Œ **Epic**

Large feature broken into smaller stories.
**Example:** â€œUser Management Systemâ€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **User Story**

Small requirement written from user perspective.
â€œAs a user, I want to reset password so that I can access my account.â€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Task / Subtask**

Development or technical work needed to complete a story.
**Example:** â€œCreate API for reset passwordâ€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Acceptance Criteria**

Conditions to confirm story is done.
**Example:** â€œOTP must expire in 5 minutes.â€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Story Points**

Complexity measurement (not time).
Used for planning velocity.

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Definition of Ready (DoR)**

Checklist before story enters a sprint.
âœ” Acceptance criteria
âœ” Estimated
âœ” Clear requirement
âœ” Dependencies resolved

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Definition of Done (DoD)**

Checklist before story is considered completed.
âœ” Code complete
âœ” Code reviewed
âœ” Unit tested
âœ” Deployed to QA
âœ” No open defects

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Sprint Goal**

Commitment/mission of the sprint.
**Example:** â€œEnable users to recover password via email.â€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Increment**

Working software produced at end of sprint.

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Velocity**

Number of story points completed by team each sprint.

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Burndown Chart**

Graph showing remaining work in sprint.

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Impediment / Blocker**

Anything stopping progress.
**Example:** â€œQA environment down.â€

---

## ğŸ“Œ **Scrum Roles**

| Role              | Responsibility            |
| ----------------- | ------------------------- |
| **Product Owner** | Requirement owner         |
| **Scrum Master**  | Process facilitator       |
| **Developer**     | Build functionality       |
| **QA**            | Test functionality        |
| **DevOps**        | CI/CD, infra, deployments |

